ITT Educational Services, Inc.

13000 North Meridian Street 
Carmel IN 46032 United States
Phone: +1 317-___-____
Fax: +1 317-___-____
http://www.ittesi.com





9
Managers




127
IT employees




$30.2MEST.
IT Budget




ITT Educational Services, Inc. is the parent company of the ITT Technical Institutes, which operates technology-oriented postsecondary institutions. The company has 140 ITT Technical Institutes locations in 38 states. The company also owns and operates Daniel Webster College.

ITT declared bankruptcy… MoreITT Educational Services, Inc. is the parent company of the ITT Technical Institutes, which operates technology-oriented postsecondary institutions. The company has 140 ITT Technical Institutes locations in 38 states. The company also owns and operates Daniel Webster College.

ITT declared bankruptcy in September, 2016.
IT Priorities:
•The IT department at ITT Educational Services, Inc. primarily focuses on the management of network services and application development.
 •The management information systems group at ITT is working to enhance its .NET environment with improved automation and systems processing.
•The… MoreIT Priorities:
•The IT department at ITT Educational Services, Inc. primarily focuses on the management of network services and application development.
 •The management information systems group at ITT is working to enhance its .NET environment with improved automation and systems processing.
•The company maintains an ongoing virtualization effort, with its applications and campus sites being migrated onto cloud services.
•The company has begun to implement a bring your own device (BYOD) program.

IT Structure:
•ITT acquired Daniel Webster College in April 2009, and the college currently has its own semi-independent IT operations led by an IT team that includes a staff of four individuals.
•Outside of the IT department, the human resources group collaborates with IT developers to manage the company's human resources information systems (HRIS).
•Following the departure of the company's CIO, the IT department is currently led by its department heads.

IT Intelligence Snippets:
2013:
•ITT heavily utilizes Cisco systems for network hardware and management solutions, and maintains its data on SQL 2008 R2 and 2012 servers.  The company's storage systems are managed on Dell SAN solutions and virtualized using VMware and Amazon cloud services.
•ITT Education is primarily a Microsoft shop, with SharePoint and Dynamics systems providing the collaboration, customer relationship management (CRM) and enterprise resource planning (ERP) systems for the company. 

2012:
•The company migrated much of its internal applications onto a cloud environment, and worked to virtualize its server environment.





